question_title: diet program varies between 5 Ibs & 10 Ibs. uniform distribution Find probability that more than 9Ibs are lost [SEP] question_content:  [SEP] best_answer: Don't you think you could have written this more clearly? 

If there is a uniform distribution of the weight w being between 5 and 10, then each of these probabilities is equal:

P5_6=P{5<=w<6}
P6_7=P{6<= w<7}
P7_8=P{7<=w<8}
P8_9=P{8<=w<9}
P9_10=P{9<=w<10} 

The sum of these is 1, so 

1=P5_6+P6_7+P7_8+P8_9+P9_10, and
P5_6=P6_7=P7_8-P8_9=P9_10

so 1=5xP9_10, so P9_10=0.2

The probability is 0.2.
